            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"sympy-gamma-nb\">\ud83e\uddee SymPy Gamma NB</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">A tiny <a href=\"https://gamma.sympy.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">SymPy Gamma</a> in a notebook: type a single\nexpression and get back a stack of <strong>cards</strong> that analyse it \u2014 simplified and\nfactored forms, roots, derivative, integral, series expansion, and a plot.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Everything below recomputes live as you edit the box.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Syntax tips:</strong></span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">You can use <code>x</code> as the variable, <code>**</code> for powers (<code>x**2</code>), <code>/</code> for\nfractions, and function names like <code>sin</code>, <code>exp</code>, <code>sqrt</code>. Implicit\nmultiplication works too, so <code>2x</code> means <code>2*x</code>.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
